92
00:06:09,875 --> 00:06:12,494
-How's it feel?
-Like there's no skin on my head!

93
00:06:12,693 --> 00:06:13,870
lf you can talk, it's out.

94
00:06:14,067 --> 00:06:16,402
-How does it look?
-Can't tell yet.

95
00:06:16,596 --> 00:06:19,148
ls it straight?
l'm not doing it again.

96
00:06:19,572 --> 00:06:21,328
Let me dry it.

97
00:06:23,475 --> 00:06:25,548
l can tell it's laying down.

98
00:06:28,436 --> 00:06:30,344
Don't take it off yet.

99
00:06:45,971 --> 00:06:47,214
Looks white, don't it?

100
00:06:47,411 --> 00:06:48,427
All right!

101
00:06:49,075 --> 00:06:50,733
Well, all root!

102
00:06:50,930 --> 00:06:51,912
All reet!

103
00:07:09,873 --> 00:07:11,784
Hit the brim with the left.

104
00:07:30,512 --> 00:07:32,813
When my mother was pregnant with me...

105
00:07:33,712 --> 00:07:37,640
...a party of Klansmen surrounded
our house in Omaha, Nebraska.

106
00:07:37,840 --> 00:07:41,386
They brandished guns and shouted
for my father to come out.

107
00:07:43,984 --> 00:07:46,635
My pregnant mother went to the door...

108
00:07:46,831 --> 00:07:49,702
...and said that my father was in
Milwaukee, preaching.

109
00:07:50,193 --> 00:07:52,461
They said that good white Christians...

110
00:07:52,656 --> 00:07:56,135
...would not stand for his
troublemaking and to get out of town.

111
00:08:13,999 --> 00:08:17,260
They broke every window with
their rifles before riding away.

112
00:08:19,055 --> 00:08:22,916
They rode off into the moonlight as
suddenly as they had come.

113
00:08:24,367 --> 00:08:28,643
My father was not a frightened Negro,
as most were and many still are today.

114
00:08:28,845 --> 00:08:31,050
He was 6 feet 4 and very strong.

115
00:08:31,247 --> 00:08:33,035
He believed, as did Marcus Garvey...

116
00:08:33,230 --> 00:08:35,531
...that freedom, independence
and self-respect...

117
00:08:35,726 --> 00:08:37,351
...wouldn't be achieved
by Negroes in America.

118
00:08:37,549 --> 00:08:42,286
--the object of building up for
themselves a great nation in Africa.

119
00:08:42,765 --> 00:08:43,747
Therefore...

120
00:08:43,949 --> 00:08:47,463
...black men should leave America and
return to their land of origin.

121
00:08:49,325 --> 00:08:51,847
My father dedicated his life
to his beliefs...

122
00:08:52,046 --> 00:08:54,697
...because four of his six brothers
died violently.

123
00:08:54,893 --> 00:08:57,707
Three killed by white men,
and one lynched.

124
00:08:57,966 --> 00:09:00,104
There were nine children in our family.

125
00:09:00,685 --> 00:09:04,101
My mother was a proud woman, an
educated woman, a strong woman.

126
00:09:05,164 --> 00:09:09,026
She was fair-skinned because her mother
was raped by a white man.

127
00:09:09,229 --> 00:09:12,742
One reason she married my father was
because he was so black.

128
00:09:13,101 --> 00:09:17,192
She hated her complexion and wanted
her children to have some color.

129
00:09:17,869 --> 00:09:22,341
I think this had a profound effect on
me then and on most Negroes today.

130
00:09:22,956 --> 00:09:27,428
Because so many of our sisters have been
raped or violated by the white man...

131
00:09:27,627 --> 00:09:31,368
...black men can't wait to get their
hands on the white man's prize:

132
00:09:31,563 --> 00:09:33,158
A white woman.

133
00:09:35,468 --> 00:09:37,954
Africa for the Africans!

134
00:09:39,626 --> 00:09:41,055
Say "Roseland."

135
00:09:42,698 --> 00:09:45,284
Showtime!

136
00:09:45,804 --> 00:09:47,941
Showtime!

137
00:10:16,234 --> 00:10:17,378
Hi, Shorty!

138
00:10:18,890 --> 00:10:19,937
You're too big!

139
00:10:20,136 --> 00:10:21,380
l'm gonna come get you.

140
00:10:27,434 --> 00:10:30,334
Come on, Shorty,
l've gotta dance!

141
00:10:40,232 --> 00:10:42,304
You in charge, boy!

142
00:10:45,064 --> 00:10:46,821
You like what you see, baby?

143
00:10:49,768 --> 00:10:50,565
Get back here!

144
00:10:50,759 --> 00:10:51,806
Go ahead, boy!

145
00:10:52,008 --> 00:10:53,632
Red, save me! Save me!

146
00:10:53,832 --> 00:10:54,626
Gotcha!

147
00:11:05,607 --> 00:11:08,421
Come on, Shorty. l wanna dance again!

148
00:13:07,618 --> 00:13:09,656
Laura sure can go, can't she?

149
00:13:09,858 --> 00:13:11,800
-l gotta go freshen up.
-All right.

150
00:13:12,002 --> 00:13:14,238
-You come on back now.
-All right, Malcolm.

151
00:13:15,009 --> 00:13:17,530
That chick is fine as May wine.

152
00:13:17,794 --> 00:13:21,021
Except she lives up on a hill
and got a grandmother too.

153
00:13:21,216 --> 00:13:24,250
She a church girl.
l don't know what l'm gonna do.

154
00:13:44,704 --> 00:13:46,231
Wanna dance?

155
00:14:11,230 --> 00:14:12,604
So what do they call you?

156
00:14:13,693 --> 00:14:14,643
Red.

157
00:14:18,271 --> 00:14:19,165
l'm Sophia.

158
00:14:19,774 --> 00:14:20,788
How you doing?

159
00:14:20,990 --> 00:14:22,746
Very well, thank you.

160
00:14:23,453 --> 00:14:25,015
l have an idea, Red.

161
00:14:27,293 --> 00:14:30,676
Why don't you take that
little girl home and come on back?

162
00:14:38,206 --> 00:14:40,244
Just walk, baby, don't run.

163
00:14:42,045 --> 00:14:43,900
lt'll be here when you get back.

164
00:14:58,812 --> 00:15:00,700
Well, l better not come in.

165
00:15:00,892 --> 00:15:02,418
l'm not stupid.

166
00:15:03,453 --> 00:15:04,400
lt's late, baby.

167
00:15:04,604 --> 00:15:07,507
l know where you're going.
l am not a total square.

168
00:15:07,709 --> 00:15:10,937
-l know what's happening--
-l gotta go home. lt's late.

169
00:15:11,132 --> 00:15:14,809
l gotta get up early in the morning.
l gotta work tomorrow.

170
00:15:17,563 --> 00:15:18,970
l'll call you tomorrow?

171
00:15:19,164 --> 00:15:20,658
What for?

172
00:15:20,923 --> 00:15:25,363
l'm not white and l don't put out,
so why would you want to call me?

173
00:15:29,403 --> 00:15:32,021
Good night, Mrs. Johnson.
l'll call you tomorrow.

174
00:16:23,449 --> 00:16:25,838
Am l the first white woman
you've been with?

175
00:16:27,865 --> 00:16:29,141
No, you ain't.

176
00:16:29,464 --> 00:16:31,537
Shit, l done had plenty.

177
00:16:33,401 --> 00:16:34,895
That isn't a whore?

178
00:16:52,248 --> 00:16:53,229
Take your time.

179
00:16:53,431 --> 00:16:56,814
Sophia's not going anywhere.

180
00:16:57,911 --> 00:16:59,285
l told you to walk...

181
00:16:59,766 --> 00:17:01,141
...don't run.

182
00:17:04,088 --> 00:17:06,159
l don't like women that talk too much.

183
00:17:10,486 --> 00:17:11,981
Who wants to talk?

184
00:17:30,261 --> 00:17:31,887
You missed me.

185
00:17:32,086 --> 00:17:33,940
Try this on for size.

186
00:17:37,877 --> 00:17:39,437
-l ducked.
-You ducked?

187
00:17:39,637 --> 00:17:41,807
You didn't! l got you
right between the toes!

188
00:17:42,005 --> 00:17:45,321
l'm tired of playing the cops.
l wanna be Bogart.

189
00:17:45,526 --> 00:17:48,275
Shorty, you're too small to be Bogart.

190
00:17:48,469 --> 00:17:50,061
l'm not too short to be Cagney.

191
00:17:53,876 --> 00:17:55,284
One more!

192
00:17:59,573 --> 00:18:02,955
You dirty, rotten, stinking copper!

193
00:18:09,077 --> 00:18:10,482
You used to be a big shot.

194
00:18:15,285 --> 00:18:17,324
There is just nothing l can do.

195
00:18:17,524 --> 00:18:20,622
-What do you mean, took his own life?
-You heard the verdict.

196
00:18:20,819 --> 00:18:25,423
Verdict? A man takes a hammer and
bashes in the back of his own head?

197
00:18:25,620 --> 00:18:27,889
Then he lays on the tracks
and kills himself?

198
00:18:28,403 --> 00:18:30,606
We only act on the verdicts,
we don't make them.

199
00:18:30,804 --> 00:18:32,625
Do you pay or don't you?

200
00:18:37,524 --> 00:18:38,864
Read the policy, ma'am.

201
00:18:39,667 --> 00:18:42,088
lt clearly states....

202
00:18:50,161 --> 00:18:51,144
Come here, Sophia.

203
00:19:00,785 --> 00:19:02,312
You're the man.

204
00:19:04,273 --> 00:19:05,614
Sit down.

205
00:19:11,536 --> 00:19:13,096
What's your story?

206
00:19:13,297 --> 00:19:16,396
You one of them white chicks
can't get enough colored studs?

207
00:19:26,704 --> 00:19:28,298
lKiss my foot.

208
00:19:30,735 --> 00:19:32,492
Go ahead, kiss it.

209
00:19:41,359 --> 00:19:42,920
Now feed me.

210
00:20:02,895 --> 00:20:04,650
That's your story, girl.

211
00:20:05,487 --> 00:20:06,948
So when you gonna holler rape?

212
00:20:07,310 --> 00:20:08,106
Me?

213
00:20:08,302 --> 00:20:10,758
Yes, you.
You would, if the time came.

214
00:20:10,958 --> 00:20:12,169
Sure you would.

215
00:20:12,878 --> 00:20:14,601
Malcolm, let me feed you.

216
00:20:15,118 --> 00:20:16,546
Come on.

217
00:20:17,358 --> 00:20:19,017
While they're hot.

218
00:20:27,021 --> 00:20:29,543
l wish your mother and father
could see you now.

219
00:20:30,221 --> 00:20:32,196
And that ofay you're gonna marry.

220
00:20:32,397 --> 00:20:34,372
l sure wish Laura could see us.

221
00:21:23,051 --> 00:21:24,774
Please, Malcolm.

222
00:21:25,547 --> 00:21:27,620
There's nobody around.

223
00:21:29,004 --> 00:21:30,693
No, this ain't right.

224
00:21:32,043 --> 00:21:34,213
-Why?
-Because you--

225
00:21:34,411 --> 00:21:37,281
No, it's because of
the white girl, isn't it?

226
00:21:37,483 --> 00:21:41,759
-lt's not because of that.
-Folks say you run around with her.

227
00:21:41,961 --> 00:21:45,607
Save it for Mr. Right. Your
grandmother's smarter than you think.

228
00:21:49,066 --> 00:21:51,486
l'm sorry she raised me that way.

229
00:21:57,514 --> 00:21:58,920
ls your mother alive?

230
00:21:59,146 --> 00:22:00,094
Yes, she's alive.

231
00:22:01,578 --> 00:22:04,425
When l was a kid, l was so poor
l thought "not for sale" ...

232
00:22:04,617 --> 00:22:06,691
...was a brand name.

233
00:22:07,337 --> 00:22:08,199
l did knock.

234
00:22:08,394 --> 00:22:09,799
Did you hear me say, "Come in"?

235
00:22:10,952 --> 00:22:13,986
There's no point in fighting about it.
l'm sorry.

236
00:22:14,250 --> 00:22:17,096
-May l sit down?
-You're nice enough to ask.

237
00:22:20,392 --> 00:22:22,814
lt's the same questions, Mrs. Little.

238
00:22:23,400 --> 00:22:26,467
-Since your husband's death...
-Murder. Murder.

239
00:22:26,824 --> 00:22:31,079
...there's a question as to whether you
can raise these children alone.

240
00:22:32,456 --> 00:22:34,399
These are my children.

241
00:22:36,041 --> 00:22:37,634
They're mine.

242
00:22:38,664 --> 00:22:40,190
And they ain't no question.

243
00:22:40,392 --> 00:22:45,127
Sometimes, Mrs. Little, candor
is the only kindness.

244
00:22:45,641 --> 00:22:47,395
All your children are delinquent...

245
00:22:47,592 --> 00:22:50,591
...and one at least,
Malcolm, is a thief.

246
00:22:50,792 --> 00:22:51,423
Get out!

247
00:22:51,623 --> 00:22:54,972
Your control over your
children is nonexistent.

248
00:22:55,175 --> 00:22:56,583
Did you hear me?

249
00:22:59,206 --> 00:23:00,416
You will regret this.

250
00:23:00,615 --> 00:23:04,706
lf you don't move through that door,
you'll be past regretting!

251
00:23:07,367 --> 00:23:10,683
We were parceled out, all of us.

252
00:23:11,303 --> 00:23:15,076
I truly believe that if ever
a state agency destroyed a family...

253
00:23:15,397 --> 00:23:16,707
...it destroyed ours.

254
00:23:17,254 --> 00:23:21,989
I was sent to a detention
home and lived at this woman's house.

255
00:23:22,246 --> 00:23:23,620
Mrs. Swerlin.

256
00:23:23,814 --> 00:23:26,813
Boys, this is Malcolm, our new guest.

257
00:23:27,206 --> 00:23:28,832
We'll treat him like a brother.

258
00:23:29,926 --> 00:23:33,154
I was special. The only
colored kid in the class.

259
00:23:33,445 --> 00:23:36,608
I became sort of a mascot,
like a pink poodle.

260
00:23:37,253 --> 00:23:40,700
I got called a nigger so much,
I didn't think it was wrong.

261
00:23:40,902 --> 00:23:42,756
I thought it was my name.

262
00:23:43,621 --> 00:23:46,686
They talked about me like I wasn't
there. Like a pedigreed dog...

263
00:23:46,885 --> 00:23:48,260
...or a horse.

264
00:23:48,998 --> 00:23:50,207
Like I was invisible.

265
00:23:50,596 --> 00:23:54,142
The important thing
is to be realistic.

266
00:23:54,340 --> 00:23:56,728
We all like you here, you know that.

267
00:23:57,316 --> 00:23:58,746
But you're a nigger...

268
00:23:58,980 --> 00:24:02,112
...and a lawyer is no realistic
goal for a nigger.

269
00:24:02,307 --> 00:24:04,795
But why, Mr. Ostrowski?

270
00:24:05,060 --> 00:24:07,329
l gets the best grades in class.

271
00:24:07,524 --> 00:24:10,819
l got voted class president.
l want to be a lawyer.

272
00:24:11,011 --> 00:24:14,012
l want you to think about
something that you can be.

273
00:24:14,531 --> 00:24:17,630
You're good with your hands,
making things.

274
00:24:18,179 --> 00:24:20,089
People would give you work. l would.

275
00:24:21,380 --> 00:24:23,136
Why not become a carpenter?

276
00:24:23,843 --> 00:24:26,264
That's a good profession for a colored.

277
00:24:27,362 --> 00:24:28,989
Wasn't your pa a carpenter?

278
00:24:30,116 --> 00:24:31,774
Jesus was a carpenter.

279
00:24:32,738 --> 00:24:35,836
People like you as a person.
You're doing real well.

280
00:24:37,633 --> 00:24:39,127
Remember what we said.

281
00:24:39,555 --> 00:24:42,010
"Nothing succeeds like success."
Say it.

282
00:24:42,210 --> 00:24:44,511
Nothing succeeds like success.

283
00:24:44,705 --> 00:24:46,528
As long as you're realistic.

284
00:24:46,722 --> 00:24:48,380
lt's not the end of the world.

285
00:24:50,849 --> 00:24:52,825
l said, "Don't...

286
00:24:53,633 --> 00:24:55,935
...let them give that boy no pig."

287
00:24:56,481 --> 00:24:58,204
It wasn't the end
of the world for me.

288
00:24:58,401 --> 00:25:00,638
But it was the beginning of the end
for my mother.

289
00:25:05,601 --> 00:25:07,935
A right cross to thejaw by Louis.

290
00:25:10,625 --> 00:25:14,237
Louis takes Conn's head back
with a right uppercut.

291
00:25:14,433 --> 00:25:15,993
Louis hits left and right.

292
00:25:16,193 --> 00:25:19,541
And Conn is down
with a right cross to thejaw!

293
00:25:19,777 --> 00:25:21,272
He's taking the count.

294
00:25:21,472 --> 00:25:24,025
Four, five, six...

295
00:25:24,736 --> 00:25:27,769
...seven. He's on his back.
Eight. Nine.

296
00:25:28,033 --> 00:25:31,742
He's getting up!
The referee says it's all over!

297
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:37,437
What in hell is going on?

298
00:25:37,791 --> 00:25:38,587
Nothing, Mr. Cooper.

299
00:25:38,784 --> 00:25:40,190
The customer's are hungry.

300
00:25:40,670 --> 00:25:42,078
Soup done finished, Mr. Cooper.

301
00:25:42,272 --> 00:25:43,931
Right, Mr. Charlie.

302
00:25:44,512 --> 00:25:45,821
The name is Mr. Cooper.

303
00:25:46,527 --> 00:25:47,607
Don't you forget it.

304
00:25:48,319 --> 00:25:49,977
Mr. Cooper.

305
00:25:53,119 --> 00:25:55,454
What's the matter with you?
You want me to get fired!

306
00:25:55,647 --> 00:25:56,858
l got a wife and six kids!

307
00:25:57,054 --> 00:25:59,357
Mr. Cooper is good white folk!

308
00:25:59,551 --> 00:26:01,884
You is a young fool!

309
00:26:10,078 --> 00:26:12,663
There'll never be another one like that!

310
00:26:14,013 --> 00:26:15,126
He's done it!

311
00:26:15,326 --> 00:26:17,561
And by a knockout...

312
00:26:17,757 --> 00:26:21,139
...and still the world's
heavyweight champion:

313
00:26:21,374 --> 00:26:23,446
Joe Louis!

314
00:26:23,647 --> 00:26:25,336
Ham and cheese!
Excuse me, sir.

315
00:26:25,534 --> 00:26:28,183
Ham and cheese here! l got coffee.

316
00:26:28,381 --> 00:26:30,902
-Lemon meringue pie.
-Hey, boy!

317
00:26:31,164 --> 00:26:34,362
-Ham and cheese.
-Yes, sir. Best in the house.

318
00:26:34,557 --> 00:26:37,209
-You're pleased with yourself.
-l aims to please, sir.

319
00:26:37,404 --> 00:26:38,484
l'm pleased to aim.

320
00:26:38,685 --> 00:26:40,179
-l like you, boy.
-Thank you.

321
00:26:44,061 --> 00:26:44,857
lKeep the change.

322
00:26:45,052 --> 00:26:47,290
Right, sir!
Ham and cheese!

323
00:26:55,133 --> 00:26:55,929
Harlem!

324
00:27:16,891 --> 00:27:19,542
And here's Joe Lewis,
back in Harlem.

325
00:27:20,091 --> 00:27:22,131
They're celebrating!
They're going crazy!

326
00:27:22,330 --> 00:27:25,397
They're dancing! They're hanging
from street signs!

327
00:27:25,594 --> 00:27:27,254
Everybody's out!

328
00:27:27,612 --> 00:27:30,512
Everyone's having a great time!
Listen to them roar!

329
00:28:04,601 --> 00:28:07,350
Joe's a credit to his race.
What a fine gentleman!

330
00:28:07,609 --> 00:28:09,496
But he's also a fine American.

331
00:28:09,690 --> 00:28:12,886
The Brown Bomber, Joe Louis!

332
00:28:15,320 --> 00:28:16,465
Hey, sugar.

333
00:28:16,728 --> 00:28:19,282
-Slow down. What's your hurry?
-No hurry.

334
00:28:19,481 --> 00:28:21,007
Let me show you something new.

335
00:28:22,104 --> 00:28:24,078
l got gold watches, diamond rings.

336
00:28:24,279 --> 00:28:26,134
Any one of these. Whatever you need.

337
00:28:26,455 --> 00:28:27,349
l don't need that.

338
00:28:27,543 --> 00:28:30,480
You need something, baby.
Whatever you need!

339
00:28:30,679 --> 00:28:32,436
A couple of these
make a player look good.

340
00:29:02,423 --> 00:29:03,698
My man!

341
00:29:03,894 --> 00:29:07,952
-The word is "excuse me," boy.
-"Excuse me" don't shine my shoes.

342
00:29:08,150 --> 00:29:09,775
Then stay out of my way.

343
00:29:12,182 --> 00:29:13,938
Old country nigger.

344
00:29:18,198 --> 00:29:19,888
What you gonna do?

345
00:29:26,261 --> 00:29:27,374
Go home to your mama?

346
00:29:37,141 --> 00:29:41,648
Nigger, don't you ever in your life
say anything against my mother!

347
00:30:02,547 --> 00:30:03,726
Give me a whiskey.

348
00:30:12,628 --> 00:30:14,221
l ordered a single, Jack.

349
00:30:14,420 --> 00:30:16,840
The double's on that gentleman, "Jack."

350
00:30:21,330 --> 00:30:22,443
Who is that?

351
00:30:23,315 --> 00:30:25,323
That's West lndian Archie.

352
00:30:25,747 --> 00:30:27,340
What's his angle?

353
00:30:28,531 --> 00:30:31,018
Some of this, some of that.

354
00:30:43,473 --> 00:30:45,132
Nothing's gonna bite you.

355
00:30:46,801 --> 00:30:48,776
You look like you're new in town.

356
00:30:48,977 --> 00:30:51,977
From what l can see,
you're pretty handy with a bottle.

357
00:30:52,177 --> 00:30:52,974
He had it coming.

358
00:30:54,481 --> 00:30:55,691
Pull up a chair.

359
00:31:05,937 --> 00:31:07,344
What do they call you?

360
00:31:07,697 --> 00:31:08,776
Red.

361
00:31:09,585 --> 00:31:10,762
And l ain't no punk.

362
00:31:11,024 --> 00:31:12,301
You better not be.

363
00:31:13,008 --> 00:31:15,595
Any cat toe you down here,
you stand up or make tracks.

364
00:31:15,792 --> 00:31:16,905
Man live by his rep.

365
00:31:17,168 --> 00:31:17,996
Better believe it.

366
00:31:19,440 --> 00:31:20,869
So what do you do?

367
00:31:21,073 --> 00:31:22,021
Working on the train.

368
00:31:23,695 --> 00:31:24,492
Like that job?

369
00:31:24,944 --> 00:31:28,424
-lKeeps me out of the Army.
-They want you, nothing'll keep you out.

370
00:31:28,625 --> 00:31:29,420
Not this boy.

371
00:31:31,280 --> 00:31:33,646
So l hear tell
you're a good man to know.

372
00:31:33,838 --> 00:31:35,781
-Where you hear that?
-Boston, where l'm from.

373
00:31:35,985 --> 00:31:37,445
lKiss my neck.

374
00:31:37,808 --> 00:31:39,269
l've never been in Beantown.

375
00:31:39,471 --> 00:31:42,189
Like the man said, a man's rep travels.

376
00:31:43,183 --> 00:31:44,458
How about that!

377
00:31:46,607 --> 00:31:47,687
You bullshitting me?

378
00:31:47,887 --> 00:31:50,788
My father told me
never bullshit a West lndian.

379
00:31:50,990 --> 00:31:52,168
Your daddy's West lndian?

380
00:31:52,367 --> 00:31:53,479
My mama.

381
00:31:54,126 --> 00:31:55,818
She's from Grenada.

382
00:31:56,110 --> 00:31:57,321
Grenada.

383
00:32:01,103 --> 00:32:01,932
l like this guy.

384
00:32:02,350 --> 00:32:04,173
l like your country.

385
00:32:04,942 --> 00:32:06,185
Grenada.

386
00:32:06,382 --> 00:32:08,838
Where'd you get them
goddamn vines you got on?

387
00:32:09,166 --> 00:32:10,660
And them shoes?

388
00:32:10,959 --> 00:32:11,754
Oh, my.

389
00:32:11,949 --> 00:32:13,323
We can do something about that.

390
00:32:13,517 --> 00:32:16,649
But he's putting a hurting
on my vision, man!

391
00:32:16,845 --> 00:32:17,959
Relax.

392
00:32:18,605 --> 00:32:19,588
How do l find you?

393
00:32:19,790 --> 00:32:20,935
You can't.

394
00:32:21,710 --> 00:32:23,019
l get ahold of you.

395
00:32:23,214 --> 00:32:25,286
All right, l'll write it down.

396
00:32:25,484 --> 00:32:27,241
Don't ever write anything down.

397
00:32:27,437 --> 00:32:29,096
File it up here.

398
00:32:29,422 --> 00:32:30,762
Like l do.

399
00:32:31,566 --> 00:32:34,826
lf the man don't have any paper,
he will never have any proof.

400
00:32:35,341 --> 00:32:36,355
Dig?

401
00:32:37,837 --> 00:32:40,324
Yeah, l dig. Right.

402
00:32:45,100 --> 00:32:46,181
Look me in the face.

403
00:32:46,380 --> 00:32:47,974
Did you just con me?

404
00:32:50,764 --> 00:32:51,811
Yes, sir.

405
00:32:52,204 --> 00:32:53,065
Why?

406
00:32:53,260 --> 00:32:54,722
Because l want in.

407
00:32:55,563 --> 00:32:58,116
lt don't take a lot to know
you're already there.

408
00:32:58,316 --> 00:32:59,909
At least he ain't lying.

409
00:33:00,108 --> 00:33:01,482
l have a run to make.

410
00:33:01,677 --> 00:33:03,912
Let me make that run
with you, Mr. Archie.

411
00:33:12,748 --> 00:33:13,696
l like your heart.

412
00:33:14,763 --> 00:33:16,356
l like your style.

413
00:33:17,258 --> 00:33:19,200
You might just do, Mr. Red.

414
00:33:19,403 --> 00:33:22,469
Unless you have to
get back to your train job.

415
00:33:22,666 --> 00:33:24,706
l've told him what to do
with that train.

416
00:33:24,907 --> 00:33:26,084
-When?
-Just now.

417
00:33:31,275 --> 00:33:32,453
All right.

418
00:33:33,163 --> 00:33:34,275
Come with me.

419
00:33:34,602 --> 00:33:36,293
l'm taking you shopping.

420
00:33:37,963 --> 00:33:39,554
Cadillac's the name.

421
00:33:40,298 --> 00:33:41,891
Sammy, man.

422
00:33:42,890 --> 00:33:44,645
-You ready?
-Good.

423
00:33:47,914 --> 00:33:49,735
Button more buttons on the jacket.

424
00:33:57,577 --> 00:33:59,617
You look good.

425
00:33:59,880 --> 00:34:01,091
But you're missing something.

426
00:34:01,288 --> 00:34:02,086
Frisk me.

427
00:34:02,729 --> 00:34:04,584
Go ahead, frisk me.

428
00:34:12,874 --> 00:34:13,985
Nothing, right?

429
00:34:19,944 --> 00:34:21,121
l'm still carrying.

430
00:34:21,479 --> 00:34:23,073
This was my first gun.

431
00:34:24,680 --> 00:34:25,760
Now it's yours.

432
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:33,829
Thank you.

433
00:34:34,023 --> 00:34:35,234
You wear it...

434
00:34:36,040 --> 00:34:37,414
...wear it so.

435
00:34:38,696 --> 00:34:40,190
Small of the back.

436
00:34:41,830 --> 00:34:43,554
Now you're outfitted.

437
00:34:45,384 --> 00:34:46,561
Ready for the streets?

438
00:34:46,760 --> 00:34:48,036
l'm ready.

439
00:34:48,838 --> 00:34:49,667
Let them come.

440
00:34:49,862 --> 00:34:54,466
Let us now turn to
the Gospel According to St. John.

441
00:34:54,727 --> 00:34:55,937
Chapter 3...

442
00:34:56,134 --> 00:34:58,589
...verse 23.

443
00:34:59,079 --> 00:34:59,874
323.

444
00:35:00,070 --> 00:35:04,772
"And John also was baptizing
in Aenon near Salim...

445
00:35:06,150 --> 00:35:09,313
...because there was much water.

446
00:35:10,694 --> 00:35:13,442
And they came...

447
00:35:14,054 --> 00:35:16,193
...and were baptized."

448
00:35:18,406 --> 00:35:19,867
313.

449
00:35:21,669 --> 00:35:22,596
255.

450
00:35:23,045 --> 00:35:24,736
lt got to be 25 1.

451
00:35:25,349 --> 00:35:26,146
403.

452
00:35:26,340 --> 00:35:28,196
l saw it in my dream.

453
00:35:28,389 --> 00:35:30,724
555.

454
00:35:30,916 --> 00:35:33,305
-What do you know?
-l feel straight.

455
00:35:34,373 --> 00:35:35,618
Your lucky day.

456
00:35:35,813 --> 00:35:37,122
Roll it for me.

457
00:35:38,533 --> 00:35:40,671
l told you, no paper, no trouble.

458
00:35:41,125 --> 00:35:42,532
l'm working on it.

459
00:35:43,557 --> 00:35:45,857
l keep my numbers in my head.

460
00:35:46,053 --> 00:35:49,794
l've never written a number down yet.
Remember that.

461
00:36:04,098 --> 00:36:05,243
Your turn.

462
00:36:11,363 --> 00:36:12,378
Easy.

463
00:36:15,874 --> 00:36:17,052
Easy.

464
00:36:18,980 --> 00:36:19,775
You there?

465
00:36:19,971 --> 00:36:21,180
lf l ain't, l'm next door.

466
00:36:21,412 --> 00:36:25,185
Nothing in this world can give you
that real deep cool.

467
00:36:25,699 --> 00:36:27,007
The girl.

468
00:36:43,298 --> 00:36:45,305
About as mellow as l can be.

469
00:36:50,529 --> 00:36:51,577
Cool enough to kill.

470
00:36:51,776 --> 00:36:53,119
l realize that.

471
00:36:55,617 --> 00:36:57,853
-Easy, easy, easy, easy.
-Stick them up.

472
00:37:01,537 --> 00:37:02,464
Archie!

473
00:37:05,056 --> 00:37:06,005
Baby?

474
00:37:11,680 --> 00:37:13,590
Malcolm, you're so funny.

475
00:37:15,935 --> 00:37:17,397
Give me some money, baby.

476
00:37:22,689 --> 00:37:24,314
Come on, baby.

477
00:37:24,543 --> 00:37:26,267
The bitch move too slow.

478
00:37:30,079 --> 00:37:33,210
Sometimes this guy
has a big ugly mouth.

479
00:37:33,407 --> 00:37:34,815
What time is it, baby?

480
00:37:35,903 --> 00:37:37,813
8:21.

481
00:37:38,048 --> 00:37:39,389
l like that. Combinate me.

482
00:37:40,030 --> 00:37:41,623
821.

483
00:37:41,824 --> 00:37:43,449
128.

484
00:37:44,639 --> 00:37:46,133
218.

485
00:37:46,366 --> 00:37:47,413
l'm taking the bet.

486
00:37:51,870 --> 00:37:53,561
Time to reload.

487
00:38:39,229 --> 00:38:42,163
l thought you said we was going
to the movies last night.

488
00:38:42,365 --> 00:38:43,226
You said that.

489
00:38:43,485 --> 00:38:45,339
l'm sorry. l say a lot of things.

490
00:38:45,563 --> 00:38:46,426
l believed you.

491
00:38:46,620 --> 00:38:50,035
Do your job now. Get me a pack
of Lucky Strikes and a cognac.

492
00:39:02,651 --> 00:39:03,763
Daniel come in yet?

493
00:39:03,964 --> 00:39:05,392
Ain't that him?

494
00:39:06,139 --> 00:39:07,087
Gorgeous!

495
00:39:07,738 --> 00:39:10,608
How you been today?
You been waiting long?

496
00:39:12,250 --> 00:39:13,973
Let me look at you.

497
00:39:15,611 --> 00:39:18,927
-l've been missing you today, Laura.
-How you doing, baby?

498
00:39:19,130 --> 00:39:22,643
l'm all right. Copacetic. Great.
Did you work today?

499
00:39:22,842 --> 00:39:25,298
No, baby, l didn't go to work.

500
00:39:25,499 --> 00:39:28,345
-l need a five-spot.
-l gave you 10 this morning.

501
00:39:28,795 --> 00:39:31,128
Give me the goddamn $5!

502
00:39:31,323 --> 00:39:32,783
lt ain't the money.
l wanna...

503
00:39:32,986 --> 00:39:34,512
...make sure you're okay.

504
00:39:34,713 --> 00:39:36,853
l gotta pay back this guy.

505
00:39:37,497 --> 00:39:38,642
l'll be right back.

506
00:39:39,929 --> 00:39:41,303
Like last time?

507
00:39:41,498 --> 00:39:43,385
l swear, l'll be right back.

508
00:39:43,577 --> 00:39:45,552
Laura, l love you.

509
00:39:53,688 --> 00:39:55,150
You know that chick?

510
00:39:57,146 --> 00:39:58,933
You a private detective now?

511
00:39:59,128 --> 00:40:00,056
Just asking.

512
00:40:00,249 --> 00:40:02,255
Don't ask me no goddamn questions.

513
00:40:02,456 --> 00:40:05,009
l ask you the questions.
You understand?

514
00:40:05,848 --> 00:40:08,150
-She come in here a lot?
-Almost every night.

515
00:40:08,345 --> 00:40:09,326
With him?

516
00:40:10,937 --> 00:40:13,303
-She know he's high?
-lf she got eyes, she do.

517
00:40:15,479 --> 00:40:16,462
She ain't hooking?

518
00:40:16,825 --> 00:40:18,580
Not yet, Red.

519
00:40:19,095 --> 00:40:22,096
But the way things are,
he'll turn her out any day now.

